    "course_title": "URBAN AND REGIONAL ECONOMICS",
    "description": "Focuses on the study of the allocation of scarce resources across space. Uses economic methods to analyze urban real  estate. Topics covered include the determinants of real estate values, the location decisions  of households and firms, land use, urban growth and agglomeration, real estate pricing, cycles, development, housing market and policies, and sustainable development.",
